**REACT**
 
javaScript library
use declarative approach(know what to build)
component based architecture


**Installation in UBUNTU**
   npx create-react-app myReactApp
   npx create-react-app myapp
   cd myapp
   npm start
   history


**Components**
Functional / Class

1) CLASS BASED COMPONENT
  [Basic Syntax]
  
 //**

  import React,{Component} from 'react';
  import ReactDom from 'react-dom'; 
  import './Demo.css';

  class Demo extends Component{

	render(){
		return
		 <div className="maindiv_style">
		 <h1>Hello {this.props.name}</h1>
		 <p>hello this is my channel</p>
		</div>
	}

}

export default Demo; 
 
**//



~JSX~
 
React has it's own virtual Dom (html like element in react (java script in the form of XML))


~PROPS~

props get passed to the component.
props are immutable 
this.props. - class component
props.      - functional component (have to pass props as arguments)

